sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP TLS
    participant Dashboard as Ray Head Dashboard<br/>8265/TCP HTTP
    participant Operator as CodeFlare Operator<br/>controller-runtime
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant InitCont as Init Container<br/>(OpenSSL)
    participant CACert as CA Secret<br/>(per-cluster)
    participant RayHead as Ray Head Node<br/>10001/TCP gRPC
    participant RayWorker as Ray Worker Node<br/>10001/TCP gRPC

    Note over User,Dashboard: Flow 1: OAuth Dashboard Access (OpenShift)
    User->>Router: GET /dashboard<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    Router->>OAuth: Forward (reencrypt)<br/>HTTPS TLS
    OAuth->>OAuth: Validate OpenShift OAuth token
    OAuth->>Dashboard: Proxy request<br/>HTTP localhost:8265
    Dashboard-->>OAuth: Dashboard response
    OAuth-->>Router: HTTPS response
    Router-->>User: Dashboard HTML

    Note over Operator,CACert: Flow 2: mTLS Certificate Bootstrap
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Watch RayCluster CRs<br/>ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: RayCluster created/updated
    Operator->>Operator: Generate RSA 2048-bit CA<br/>(crypto/x509, self-signed, 1yr)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create CA Secret<br/>ca-secret-{cluster}
    Note over InitCont,CACert: Pod admission (webhook injects init containers)
    InitCont->>CACert: Mount CA cert + key<br/>volume mount
    InitCont->>InitCont: OpenSSL: generate server cert<br/>signed by cluster CA with SANs
    InitCont-->>RayHead: Server cert ready<br/>in shared volume

    Note over RayHead,RayWorker: Flow 3: mTLS Ray Communication
    RayHead->>RayWorker: gRPC 10001/TCP<br/>mTLS (per-pod certs)
    RayWorker->>RayHead: gRPC 10001/TCP<br/>mTLS (per-pod certs)

    Note over Operator,K8sAPI: Flow 4: Network Policy Enforcement
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicy (head)<br/>allow same-cluster, namespace, monitoring
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicy (worker)<br/>allow same ray.io/cluster label only
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Route (dashboard)<br/>reencrypt TLS
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Route (rayclient)<br/>passthrough TLS
